      <guid>https://beardog-ukr.github.io/cocos2dx-examples/en/post/memory-actions/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Since we already know about &lt;a href=&#34;https://beardog-ukr.github.io/cocos2dx-examples/en/post/basic-actions/&#34;&gt;actions&lt;/a&gt; and other &lt;a href=&#34;https://beardog-ukr.github.io/cocos2dx-examples/en/post/basic-actions/&#34;&gt;basic things&lt;/a&gt;, now we can think about correct memory usage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To illustrate it we&amp;rsquo;ll create a &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/beardog-ukr/cocos2dx-examples/blob/master/examples/AdvancedActions/Classes/MemoryDemoScene.cpp&#34;&gt;simple scene&lt;/a&gt; with one sprite and one button. After pressing the button the sprite will out of the scene and then it should be removed somehow.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
